laboratory_examinations.findings: Visualized lung fields demonstrate mild dependent bibasilar atelectasis. The liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation throughout with no evidence of focal lesions or biliary dilatation. The pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands are normal. The kidneys are of normal size with no evidence of stones or hydronephrosis. The appendix is fluid-filled and dilated, measuring up to 1.3 cm with evidence of pelvic and right lower quadrant fat stranding and inflammatory changes. Multiple prominent retroperitoneal lymph nodes are likely reactive. There is a moderate degree of free pelvic fluid.
